records.addlTxt:
Defendant Jared Foster Stromme in court with attorney Darryl E. Smith.  Defendant Jared Foster Stromme in custody.  Nicholas Steven Cerwin for Marissa Santiago appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk:  AA.

Defendant  advised that if he is not a US citizen deportation is possible.   Defendant changes plea to GUILTY. Defendant examined as to his plea, advised of his Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty. Court found that defendant freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived his rights. Plea questionnaire received and filed. Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea. Court found defendant guilty as charged in the information and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record. Defendant is advised he is a convicted felon and may not possess any firearms; also defendant is advised he is unable to vote in any election until his civil rights are restored.

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  

The Court ordered the Defendant to:
-Serve 7 months in the House of Correction, consecutive to any other sentence with credit for 77 days time served.  Huber privileges pursuant to Sec. 303.08 Wis. Stats to apply for work, work crews, AODA treatment and Day Reporting Center and any treatment deemed appropriate.
-Court costs and victim/witness surcharges are to be paid by April 17, 2018; nonpayment penalty shall be a civil judgment
-Defendant is to provide a DNA sample and pay related surcharge by April 17, 2018; nonpayment penalty shall be a civil judgment
-Restitution set at zero

Court has no objection to Electronic Monitoring.
Court has no objection to defendant being accepted by Waukesha County Jail to serve sentence.

Court advised the defendant that as a convicted felon he may no longer use or possess any firearms; also he may not vote in any election until his civil rights have been restored.
